'''''Worlds at War''''' is a 1989 video game published by [[Lyric Software]], and was republished in 1991 by [[RAW Entertainment]].

==Gameplay==
''Worlds at War'' is a game in which the player and an opponent conquer the planets in a region of space.<ref name="CGW70"/>

==Reception==
Bob Proctor reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "Worlds At War (WAW) is not spectacular but is well done and workable. The concept isn't novel but it works."<ref name="CGW70">{{cite magazine |last=Proctor |first=Bob |title=Conflict in the Cosmos: "Worlds At War" From Lyric |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=April 1990 |volume=1 |issue=70 |pages=54, 62}}</ref>

